6/greens_sq.jpg?t=1300274685&amp;s=11" alt="They're known as a down-home side dish, but greens also liven up soups, salads, omelets and more."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/03/21/134564185/you-dont-have-to-be-southern-to-love-greens">Eating O' The Greens: Beyond Southern Side Dishes</a></h3><p>They're known as a down-home side dish, but greens also liven up soups, salads, omelets and more.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/03/14/134367508/celebrating-the-pies-of-march"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/03/08/piplate_sq.jpg?t=1300102482&amp;s=11" alt="Before the green beer starts flowing, there's Pi Day (March 14), a pastry-laden homage to math."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/03/14/134367508/celebrating-the-pies-of-march">Celebrating The Pies Of  March</a></h3><p>Before the green beer starts flowing, there's Pi Day (March 14), a pastry-laden homage to math.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/03/03/134167591/welcome-fruit-to-savory-dishes"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/03/01/savoryfruit_sq.jpg?t=1299008968&amp;s=11" alt="The sweet flavors of fresh and dried fruits liven up a meaty main dish or even a veggie side."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/03/03/134167591/welcome-fruit-to-savory-dishes">Welcome Fruit To Savory Dishes</a></h3><p>The sweet flavors of fresh and dried fruits liven up a meaty main dish or even a veggie side.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/02/23/133965525/theres-more-to-okra-than-frying"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/02/22/okramasala2_sq.jpg?t=1298405473&amp;s=11" alt="Food writer Monica Bhide's slime-busting tips take okra beyond the traditional Southern fried fare."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/02/23/133965525/theres-more-to-okra-than-frying">There's More To Okra Than Frying</a></h3><p>Food writer Monica Bhide's slime-busting tips take okra beyond the traditional Southern fried fare.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/02/17/133779706/totally-tuber-rugged-root-veggies-make-a-splash"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/02/15/rootbasket_sq.jpg?t=1297797151&amp;s=11" alt="Despite homely exteriors, celeriac, sun chokes, jicama and others are stepping into the limelight."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/02/17/133779706/totally-tuber-rugged-root-veggies-make-a-splash">Totally Tubers: Rugged Winter Veggies Take Root</a></h3><p>Despite homely exteriors, celeriac, sun chokes, jicama and others are stepping into the limelight.</p></div></div><p class="more"><a href="http://www.npr.org/series/kitchen-window/">more</a></p></div>

